snippet: Groundbreaking dropped 11 percent to a seasonally adjusted annual pace of 1.06 million units last month, the lowest level since March, the Commerce Department said.
abstract: Commerce Department reports housing starts fell 11 percent in October to seasonally adjusted annual rate of 1.06 million units.
lead_paragraph: Groundbreaking dropped 11 percent to a seasonally adjusted annual pace of 1.06 million units last month, the lowest level since March, the Commerce Department said.

headline.main: Housing Starts Fall to Seven-Month Low
headline.print_headline: U.S. Housing Starts Fall to a Seven-Month Low
